“They lived their life in circles,
A clustered round the warmth.”

We inherited the culture of meeting circles from the Art of Hosting. They turned out to be invaluable to build trust, openness and connection in the house and beyond. Applying them to decision making gave us the circles of consensus and of proposals, our honest attempts to create and maintain a horizontal organisational structure.
